===================================================================
m210 - Delete and download notes stored in Pegasus NoteTaker Tablet
===================================================================

.. contents::

Description
===========

The Code Grove m210 project provides tools for downloading and
deleting notes from Pegasus Mobile NoteTaker devices.

General information
===================

- **Author**: @PACKAGE_AUTHOR@
- **Homepage**: @PACKAGE_URL@
- **License**: GPLv3+ (see COPYING for details)
- **Version**: @VERSION@

Build requirements
==================

- udev library development files: (Ubuntu: ``apt-get install libudev-dev``)

Runtime requirements
====================

- Linux kernel 2.6.x
- usbhid module installed::

    modprobe -i usbhid

Downloading
===========

- Ubuntu package: https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove
- Tarball is available at: @PACKAGE_URL@releases/m210-@VERSION@.tar.gz
- Tarballs of every release at: @PACKAGE_URL@releases/
- Latest sources from public git-repository: http://github.com/tuos/m210/ ::

    git clone git://github.com/tuos/m210.git

Installing
==========

Ubuntu
------

The recommended way to install m210 is to
`add it's PPA to your system <https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove>`_.
This allows you to treat m210 as any other Ubuntu package.

Other systems
-------------

The install-procedure adheres the "standard"::

  ./configure
  make && make install

